Package: biljouR
Type: Package
Title: A Daily Forest Water Balance Model (BILJOU-Equivalent)
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("biljouR", "contributors", role = c("aut", "cre"),
    email = "you@example.org")
Description: An open re-implementation in R of the lumped daily forest water
    balance model BILJOU (Granier, Breda, Biron & Villette, 1999, Ecological
    Modelling 116:269-283), as documented by INRAE UMR Silva. The model runs
    at a daily time step and computes canopy transpiration, rainfall
    interception, understorey/soil evaporation, multi-layer soil water content
    with macro-/micro-porosity drainage, and drought indices (number of stress
    days, water-stress index Is, intensity, precocity). A Penman potential
    evapotranspiration helper is provided. This package is an independent
    re-implementation for research and teaching; it is not produced or endorsed
    by INRAE. For authoritative simulations use the official tool at
    <https://appgeodb.nancy.inrae.fr/biljou/>.
License: GPL-3
Encoding: UTF-8
Depends: R (>= 3.5.0)
Suggests: testthat (>= 3.0.0), knitr, rmarkdown, ggplot2, sf, terra
VignetteBuilder: knitr
RoxygenNote: 7.2.3
